I'd prefer to just keep the "x" in the cli parameter name. I don't think we need to propagate the fact that some CLI option is hidden / experimental all the way through the code.  So, something like:
String INTEROP_GENESIS_TIME_OPTION_NAME = "--x-interop-genesis-time";

where we keep the "x" just in the string value for the cli argument name.

